FBIS4-51932 "dreas087__a94007" FBIS-EAS-94-087-A Daily Report 5 May 1994 ANNEX Japan Kakizawa Criticizes Nagano Remark Kakizawa Criticizes Nagano Remark OW0505110294 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 5 May 94 Morning Edition p 3--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW0505110294 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN Japanese BFN [By correspondent Hiroki Fukuta] [Text] Jerusalem, 4 May -- Commenting on Justice Minister Shigeto Nagano's remark that the 1937 Nanjing atrocity [Nankin gyakusatsu] is a fabrication, Foreign Minister Koji Kakizawa, who is visiting Israel, told a group of Japanese correspondents on 4 May: "Japan should be engaged in soul-searching over its past act of aggression. If the justice minister's remark has caused a misunderstanding among Japan's neighboring nations, as foreign minister I will work to dispel that misunderstanding."
